    "plan_content": "## Implementation Plan: Ollama Model Rename Feature\n\nHere's what I found from studying the codebase and what I'm planning to implement:\n\n---\n\n### Existing patterns confirmed\n\n- **`CopyRequest`** (`api/types.go:761`) â€” two fields: `Source`/`Destination` with json tags; this is the exact template for `RenameRequest`\n- **`Client.Copy()`** (`api/client.go:380`) â€” calls `c.do(ctx, http.MethodPost, \"/api/copy\", req, nil)`; `Rename()` will mirror this identically\n- **`CopyHandler`** (`server/routes.go:1446`) â€” JSON bind â†’ `model.ParseName()` + `IsValid()` â†’ `getExistingName()` â†’ `CopyModel()` \n- **`DeleteHandler`** (`server/routes.go:1055`) â€” uses `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(n)` â†’ `m.Remove()` â†’ `m.RemoveLayers()`\n- **`/api/copy` route** registered at line 1698 in `GenerateRoutes()`'s \"Create\" section\n- **`copyCmd`** defined at line 2257, registered in `rootCmd.AddCommand()` at line 2345\n\n---\n\n### Plan: 7 edits across 4 files\n\n| # | File | What |\n|---|------|------|\n| 1 | `api/types.go` | Add `RenameRequest{Source, Destination string}` after `CopyRequest` |\n| 2 | `api/client.go` | Add `Rename(ctx, *RenameRequest) error` method after `Copy()` |\n| 3 | `server/routes.go` | Add `RenameHandler` method after `CopyHandler` |\n| 4 | `server/routes.go` | Register `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)` after `/api/copy` |\n| 5 | `cmd/cmd.go` | Add `RenameHandler` function after `CopyHandler` |\n| 6 | `cmd/cmd.go` | Add `renameCmd` cobra.Command after `copyCmd` in `NewCLI()` |\n| 7 | `cmd/cmd.go` | Register `renameCmd` in `rootCmd.AddCommand()` between `copyCmd` and `deleteCmd` |\n\n### `RenameHandler` logic flow\n1. Bind JSON â†’ 400 on missing/bad body\n2. Empty `Source`/`Destination` fields â†’ 400\n3. `model.ParseName()` + `!IsValid()` â†’ 400 with `errtypes.InvalidModelNameErrMsg`\n4. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` â€” if err == nil â†’ **409 Conflict** (\"destination model 'X' already exists\")\n5. `CopyModel(src, dst)` â€” `os.ErrNotExist` â†’ **404**, other error â†’ 500\n6. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` â†’ get manifest\n7. `m.Remove()` + `m.RemoveLayers()` â†’ 500 if either fails\n8. `c.JSON(200, gin.H{\"status\": \"success\"})`\n\n**No new imports needed** â€” all required packages (`manifest`, `model`, `errtypes`, `os`, `fmt`, `errors`) are already imported in `routes.go`.",
